---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Members
description: Secure access to Snow White Laundry dashboards, interactive tools, and Operator OS resources.
permalink: /members/
---
<section class="section page-hero page-hero--compact">
  <div class="container page-hero__inner">
    <p class="eyebrow">Members area</p>
    <h1>SWL Command</h1>
    <p class="lead">Log in with your magic link to access dashboards, tools, and playbooks. Alignment before acceleration.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section members">
  <div class="container members__wrap" data-members-app>
    <div class="members__panel guest-only" id="members-auth-panel">
      <h2>Request a magic link</h2>
      <p>Use the email connected to your Operator OS account.</p>
      <form class="members-form" id="members-login-form">
        <label>
          <span>Email</span>
          <input id="members-email" type="email" name="email" autocomplete="email" required placeholder="you@example.com"/>
        </label>
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn--primary" id="members-login-button">Send magic link</button>
        <p class="form-status__text" id="members-auth-message" role="status" aria-live="polite"></p>
      </form>
      <p class="members__hint">Need access? Email <a href="mailto:{{ site.contactEmail }}">{{ site.contactEmail }}</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="members__panel auth-only" id="members-authenticated">
      <header class="members__welcome">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Signed in</p>
          <h2>Hello, <span id="members-user-email">member</span>.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="members__actions">
          <button class="btn btn--ghost" id="members-refresh">Refresh data</button>
          <button class="btn btn--secondary" id="members-logout">Log out</button>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="members__notice" id="members-pending-notice">
        <p>You are signed in, but your membership flag is still pending. Contact the studio if you need immediate access.</p>
        <a class="btn btn--primary" href="mailto:{{ site.contactEmail }}">Request access</a>
      </div>

      <div class="members-hub member-only" id="members-hub">
        <nav class="role-switcher" aria-label="Select role view">
          <button type="button" class="role-switcher__btn is-active" data-role="owner">Owner</button>
          <button type="button" class="role-switcher__btn" data-role="staff">Staff</button>
          <button type="button" class="role-switcher__btn" data-role="investor">Investor</button>
        </nav>

        <section class="hub-section">
          <header class="hub-section__header">
            <h3>Dashboards</h3>
            <p>Real-time visibility across build, finance, and operations. Each module respects the minimum viable data principle.</p>
          </header>
          <div class="dashboard-grid">
            <article class="dashboard-card" data-role="owner staff">
              <h4>Build Tracker</h4>
              <p>Milestones, contractors, and capital commitments with live variance alerts.</p>
              <iframe src="https://dashboards.openpeople.studio/swl/build" title="SWL Build Dashboard" loading="lazy"></iframe>
            </article>
            <article class="dashboard-card" data-role="owner investor">
              <h4>Finance Ledger</h4>
              <p>P&amp;L snapshots, liquidity runway, and ethical guardrails for spend approvals.</p>
              <iframe src="https://dashboards.openpeople.studio/swl/finance" title="SWL Finance Dashboard" loading="lazy"></iframe>
            </article>
            <article class="dashboard-card" data-role="owner staff">
              <h4>Operations Pulse</h4>
              <p>Service rituals, guest feedback loops, and staff capacity planning.</p>
              <iframe src="https://dashboards.openpeople.studio/swl/operations" title="SWL Operations Dashboard" loading="lazy"></iframe>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="hub-section">
          <header class="hub-section__header">
            <h3>Interactive zone</h3>
            <p>Micro-tools that help operators explore scenarios before making the call.</p>
          </header>
          <div class="tool-grid">
            <article class="tool-card" data-role="owner investor">
              <h4>What-if runway</h4>
              <p>Adjust headcount, pricing, or capital injections to see runway shifts in real time.</p>
              <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="https://tools.openpeople.studio/runway" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Launch tool →</a>
            </article>
            <article class="tool-card" data-role="owner staff">
              <h4>Menu margin simulator</h4>
              <p>Balance guest experience with profitability. Model changes without breaking the brand.</p>
              <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="https://tools.openpeople.studio/menu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Launch tool →</a>
            </article>
            <article class="tool-card" data-role="owner staff">
              <h4>Vendor payment planner</h4>
              <p>Automate ethical payment cadences with alerts for variance or consent issues.</p>
              <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="https://tools.openpeople.studio/vendor" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Launch tool →</a>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="hub-section">
          <header class="hub-section__header">
            <h3>Docs &amp; playbooks</h3>
            <p>Operator OS references, updated as the pilot evolves. All documents respect the privacy model agreed on during onboarding.</p>
          </header>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li data-role="owner"><a href="https://docs.openpeople.studio/swl/operator-os" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Operator OS handbook</a></li>
            <li data-role="owner staff"><a href="https://docs.openpeople.studio/swl/service-manual" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Service rituals manual</a></li>
            <li data-role="investor"><a href="https://docs.openpeople.studio/swl/investor-update" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Investor summary</a></li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section safety">
  <div class="container safety__inner">
    <h2>Security &amp; privacy</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Supabase protects access with email-based magic links and refresh tokens.</li>
      <li>Role claims (owner, staff, investor) flow through the Netlify guard function before content unlocks.</li>
      <li>Dashboards load only after authentication; iframes are sandboxed and lazy-loaded.</li>
      <li>Data minimization by default — we only store what is required to run the pilot.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<script type="module" src="/assets/js/members.js"></script>
